# =>< snippets/stars_light_sequence
~ stars_light_success
do Character.play_audio("task1_success")
Sam: Awesome job, partner! Look at all the bright things you put in space! Now let’s go to Planet Stardust, press the GO button to get closer to finding Lucky!
set screen = "start_button"
[next=2]


# "Navigate the Spaceship (Practice)"
~ task2_practice
set screen = "idle"


~ task2_intro
do Character.play_audio("task2_intro")
Sam: Our next task is to find Planet Stardust! To help us get to Planet Stardust, we’ll need the help of the Command Centre to steer our ship. Like before, you’ll listen to the computer and repeat the directions with your voice loud and clear! The computer will send your voice to the Command Centre to steer our ship.

do Character.play_audio("task2_command_center")
Sam: The Command Centre is very picky and will only follow directions if you repeat the commands in EXACTLY the same way you heard them. Let’s hear an example of a space cadet not repeating the command right. 

do Character.play_audio("click_the_red_button_to_hear_it")
Sam: Click the RED button to hear it. 

set screen = "start_button_red"
[next=2]
set screen = "failure"
do Character.play_audio("oh_no_did_you_hear_that")
Sam: Oh no, did you hear that? 
set screen = "idle"


~ task2_bad_example
do Character.play_audio("task2_bad_example")
Sam: That space cadet didn’t do the best job of repeating EXACTLY what they heard. Let’s hear it again to see where they went wrong! Press the red button again. 
set screen = "start_button_red"
[next=2]
set screen = "failure"
do Character.play_audio("task2_bad_example_high_lows")
Sam: Did you hear that? The space cadet said the right words, but didn’t copy the ^highs^ and ~lows~ of the voice. 
set screen = "idle"


~ task2_good_example
do Character.play_audio("task2_good_example")
Sam: For the Command Centre to move our ship, we have to repeat the words in the exact same way we hear them.   Let’s make sure we do a better job. Click the green button to hear a space cadet repeating it back exactly right. 
set screen = "start_button"
[next=2]
set screen = "success"
[next=2]
set screen = "idle"
do Character.play_audio("task2_example_again")
Sam: That time, the space cadet did a great job of repeating the words AND the ^highs^ and ~lows~ of the voice. Click the green button to hear the example again. 
set screen = "start_button"
[next=2]
set screen = "success"
[next=2]
set screen = "idle"


~ task2_ready_or_repeat
do Character.play_audio("task2_ready_or_repeat")
Sam: Perfect! Are you ready to communicate with the Command Centre to move our ship to Planet Stardust? Remember, we have to move our voice high and low just like the command to steer our ship. Let your Flight Engineer know if you are ready or if you would like to hear the examples again. 
# experimenter will decide if participant needs to loop back to 1st bad imitation example


~ task2_ready_to_go
do Character.play_audio("task2_ready_to_go")
Sam: OK, here we go! Remember that the Command Centre is very sensitive, so repeat what the computer says exactly. Once you repeat after the computer, I’ll click the GREEN button to send the directions to the Command Centre and we can see if our ship moves! I’ll have a seat and let you take control!
set level = "warp"
=>< snippets/stars_warp_sequence
#12 Phrases – 6 song, 6 speech randomized (see list of sentences on last page)*


~ task2_arrived
do Character.play_audio("task2_arrived")
Sam: Awesome job, partner! Thanks for steering the ship so well! Look, it’s Planet Stardust! To use our spaceship to look around, press the Landing Button.
set screen = "start_button"
[next=1]
set level = "landing"
[next=10]


~ task2_landed
do Character.play_audio("task2_found_planet_stardust")
Sam: We did it - we found Planet Stardust! 
do Character.play_audio("task2_alien_intro")
Sam: I don’t see Lucky, but I do see something else! It looks like there are aliens on Planet Stardust!
do Character.play_audio("task2_aliens_ask_lucky")
Sam: They look really friendly, I think they are nice! Let’s ask them if they have seen Lucky or know where Lucky the Llama is. 


~ task2_alien_language
do Character.play_audio("task2_alien_language")
Sam: Aliens on Planet Stardust only speak in beeping sounds so the computer will tell us how to talk to them in their language to find out where Lucky is. Listen to the computer and repeat back the alien beeps as best as you can.
set screen = "computer"
[next=2]


# 10 stimuli – 5 pure tones, 5 intervals?*
~ task2_success
do Character.play_audio("task2_success")
Sam: You did a great job! The aliens said Lucky the Llama is over there – look, they’re bringing Lucky to us! Now the only thing left to do is take Lucky back to the Space Station.


# blast off and fade to intro (station)
~ mission_success
do Character.play_audio("mission_success")
Sam: You made it back to the Space Station - great job today! Thanks for bringing Lucky the Llama back home from Planet Stardust safely. You are a great Astronaut! Come back any time!


~ complete
System: Session Complete. Go ahead and press 'End Session', and then 'Confirm'.
=> END